sub_title: Student Computer Science & AI at Utrecht University
summary:
I'm an endlessly curious and skilled tech geek who loves to work on solving challenging technical problems using cutting-edge and innovative technologies such as deep learning. My double Master's degree helped develop me into a skilled computational and algorithmic thinker and made me proficient in machine learning and deep learning using multimedia data.

My mission is to find AI applications that benefit society and can help tackle some of the worldwide problems facing humanity. My preferred method is to address these problems at their source, the human mind. I'm interested in topics related to the brain, neuro and mental health and psychedelics, which will likely play a crucial role in the future. I believe there is great therapeutic potential in experiential therapies, incorporating tailored music and art with a facilitating, monitoring and aiding role for technology.

Language is another powerful medium for communication which contains 
meaningful information about what goes on in the human mind and the collective. This makes Natural Language Processing an invaluable tool for bridging the gap between first and third-person perspectives.
I'm fascinated by new technological advancements in the field of VR/AR and brain-computer interfaces, which will radically shift the ways in which humans and machines interact. 

My passions include art, programming and math. I'm always seeking to explore, learn more, share knowledge, and expand the consciousness of the individual and the collective.
